</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,1400]" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">
We include three 
<collectingCountry box="[395,545,1159,1184]" name="New Zealand" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pérez &amp; Del Río, 2017" authorityName="Pérez &amp; Del Río" authorityYear="2017" box="[669,771,1159,1184]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Kolmeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="17" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[669,771,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Kolmeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Powell" authorityYear="1938" box="[787,1037,1159,1184]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Pleuromeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="murdochi">
<emphasis box="[787,1037,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Pleuromeris murdochi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Powell" box="[1052,1348,1159,1184]" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" refString="Powell, A. W. (1938) A Pliocene Molluscan faunule from Castle Point. Records of the Auckland Institute and Museum, 2 (3), 157 - 164." type="journal article" year="1938">Powell 1938: pl. 39, fig. 6</bibRefCitation>
) (upper Pliocene, Castle Point Formation), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laws" authorityYear="1940" box="[569,862,1196,1221]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Pleuromeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditoida" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="paucicostata">
<emphasis box="[569,862,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Pleuromeris paucicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Laws" box="[883,1133,1196,1221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" refString="Laws, C. R. (1940) The Waitotaran faunule at Kaawa Creek. Part 3. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 69, 427 - 447." type="journal article" year="1940">Laws 1940: figs 7–8</bibRefCitation>
) (upper Pliocene–Recent, Nukumaru Beds) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marwick" authorityYear="1924" box="[408,836,1231,1256]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Venericardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marshalli" subGenus="Pleuromeris">
<emphasis box="[408,552,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Venericardia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[572,709,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Pleuromeris</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[729,836,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">marshalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marwick" box="[854,1222,1231,1256]" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" refString="Marwick, J. (1924) Palaeontological notes on some Pliocene Mollusca from Hawke's Bay. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute, 55, 191 - 202." type="journal article" year="1924">Marwick 1924: pl. 16, figs 1–2</bibRefCitation>
) (upper Pliocene– Recent, Petane Clays). These species share with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ihering-Ihering" authorityYear="1907" box="[702,873,1268,1293]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Venericardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tehuelchana">
<emphasis box="[702,873,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">K. tehuelchana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the same outline, the straight right anterior tooth, the right middle tooth slightly inclined posteriorly, and 9 to 15 wide radial ribs separated by wide intercostal spaces. As the 
<collectingCountry box="[320,471,1340,1365]" name="New Zealand" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
species are not older than Nukumaruan (upper Pliocene, 2–1.2 Ma sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Haywick" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" refString="Haywick, D., Lowe, D., Beu, A. G., Henderson, R. &amp; Carter, R. (1991) Pliocene- Pleistocene (Nukumaruan) lithostratigraphy of the Tagoio block, and origin of sedimentary cyclicity, central Hawke's Bay, New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Geology and Geophysics, 34, 213 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00288306.1991.9514459" type="journal article" year="1991">
Haywick 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ihering-Ihering" authorityYear="1907" box="[267,436,1375,1400]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Venericardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tehuelchana">
<emphasis box="[267,436,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">K. tehuelchana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(lower Pliocene) becomes the oldest member of the genus.
</paragraph>
